A pioneer of bebop drumming died August 16, 2007. Max Roach, along with the likes of Charles Mingus, John Coltrane, Charlie Parker, Thelonius Monk and of course, Dizzy Gillespie was one of the pioneers of the form of jazz we know as bebop. His influence and technique will be sorely missed.
